1 One of the worst hotels that I have ever stayed in. We paid for 4 nights online for s specific room. We drove in from Northern California and when we got here we went to go check in they told us that they did not have a room. They finally found one after 30 minutes and it was a room we did not even pay for. The food is awful here, you can get a better meal at Mcdonalds. The service is bad and the staff not very nice, and they are untrained. $24.00 for a small pot of coffee is what they wanted to charge me. After balking at that price I got it for 12. The maid service is the worst, they did not change the sheets, they did not replenish the coffee or the cups, they just did a quick vacuum. Some of the garbage from the table not removed. I can say the beds were comfortable so I slept like a baby. Beware do not eat the hotel food. If you drink coffee make sure they replenish the cups and the coffee, they did neither for us.  The WIFI in the rooms is extremely slow, the lobby is better.  There are better hotels for the price that they are asking for this one. It is slightly overpriced for what you get.
