3 This property is very conveniently located next to a great shopping village, San Tan, is just off the 202, for quick access to most eastern areas of Phoenix, and is A solidly decent property, meaning while it lacks all the known grandeur of a Hilton.  The staff are wonderful at the front desk, the housekeeping team is professional and every area of the property is well kept, but it doesn't go over the top to impress like other Hilton hotels.  Parking isn't the greatest, but tier is still considerable undeveloped land to the right of the property.
